DESCRIPTION
  • All stages sold in pairs
  • For home use only
  • Compatible with the PowerBlock U-90
  • Starts at 5-50 lbs. and expands to 70 and 90 lbs. per hand with 2 add-on kits
  • Replaces 28 pairs of dumbbells or 2565 lbs of free weights
  • Increments achieved: 2.5 (adder weight), 5, 7.5, 10, 15, 17.5, 20, 25, 27.5, 30, 35, 37.5, 40, 45, 47.5, 50, 55, 57.5, 60, 65, 67.5, 70, 75, 77.5, 80, 85, 87.5 and 90 lbs per hand
  • Dimensions 12.5″L x 7″W x 7.25″H

Similar Product: PowerBlock Pro 100 EXP Dumbbell Set

FEATURES
  • Urethane coated steel plates provide smooth and quiet performance.
  • The open draft of the interior surface maximizes the range of motion and increases ergonomics with the contoured rubber grip.
  • The 'Auto-Lock' lever on the handle is a simple way to make micro adjustments in 2.5 lbs. increments by removing two chrome ballast weights within the lower tubes. To remove the inner weights tilt the handle back so the weights don't spill out, then pull the lever down. Carefully remove the inner weights and put them in the storage slots on the stand. Then drop the handle back in the weight stack to close the lever, or do it manually. To add the weights back into the handle reverse the process.
  • The color bands on the rails correspond with the weight chart on the handle to show what will be selected.
  • This is how the magic happens! Adjust weights quickly to keep workouts flowing by using the pin to select different rails. For example, moving the pin to the bottom selects all the weight plates. The pin is super strong polypropylene and rated for a 500lbs. max load. Magnets inside the pin hold it securely once inserted completely.

Rated 4 out of 5

Awkward shape for some exercise, great otherwise!

Pros:

- Seem sturdy

- Lots of weight increments

- Size adapts to weight

- Shipping came fast

Cons:

- Awkward/ dangerous for skull crushers (no real grip when holding both dumbbells together)

- Awkward for two hands triceps pullover / other two hands pullover. (No space in the case to fit both hands and get the right pull angle. You can flip the dumbbell and hold it by the two circular columns, but I get scared of breaking em as I didn't see any official "do or don't" with.

- No 2.5, 12.5, 22.5, 32.5, 42.5 and so on. Some lifting increments may be harder, but not the end of the world.

All in all, probably should've tried the newer Snode ad80 before purchasing this, but time will tell of I made the right decision !

DESCRIPTION
The PowerBlock Commercial Pro 100 EXP Adjustable Dumbbell is the perfect addition to any commercial gym or home workout space. With a maximum weight of 100 pounds per hand, you'll have the versatility to adjust your weight to meet any strength training challenge.

The PowerBlock Pro 100 EXP can be converted into an adjustable kettlebell using the Pro 100 Series Kettlebell Handle. Coming soon, the EZ Curl Bar and Straight Bar attachments will be available for even more versatility.

These 100 pound adjustable dumbbells are the only adjustable dumbbells trusted in training facilities of pro teams across all leagues and in NCAA training facilities.

The PowerBlock Pro 100 EXP adjustable dumbbell set starts with stage 1 at 40 pounds with the option to add 3 additional expansion kits to get to 60, 80, or 100 pounds. Scale up or down as needed to customize your workouts.

SPECIFICATIONS
  • Stage 1: 5-40 pounds
  • With Stage 2: 40-60 pounds
  • With Stage 3: 60-80 pounds
  • With Stage 4: 80-100 pounds
  • Compact size: 19.2” L x 7.6” W x 7.7” H
  • Adjustable in 2.5-lb. or 5-lb. increments
  • Sold in pairs
WARRANTY
  • 5 year limited warranty

PowerBlock

PowerBlock Pro 32 Adjustable Dumbbell Set

Rated 5.0 out of 5
3 Reviews Based on 3 reviews
$399.00 Regular price $425.00 Sale price

Starting at $13/mo with Affirm. Learn more

/

 The PowerBlock Pro 32 Adjustable Dumbbell set has a weight range of 4-32lbs per hand, gives every 4 lb increment, and replaces 8 pairs of dumbbells in the space of 1 pair. These weights are extremely easy to use, with selector pins that let you change weights easily, similar to gym exercise machines. It's a great space saver; more compact and balanced than traditional dumbbells.  

  • Features
  • Specifications
Features


  1. Weight Stacks:   Urethane-coated steel plates provide smooth and quiet performance.
  2. Handle:   The open draft of the interior surface maximizes the range of motion and increases ergonomics with the contoured rubber grip.
  3. Auto-Lock:   The 'Auto-Lock' lever on the handle is a simple way to make micro-adjustments in 2.5 lbs. increments by removing two chrome ballast weights within the lower tubes. To remove the inner weights tilt the handle back so the weights don't spill out, then pull the lever down. Carefully remove the inner weights and put them in the storage slots on the stand. Then drop the handle back in the weight stack to close the lever, or do it manually. To add the weights back into the handle reverse the process.
  4. Side Rails:   The colour bands on the rails correspond with the weight chart on the handle to show what will be selected.
  5. Selector Pin:   This is how the magic happens! Adjust weights quickly to keep workouts flowing by using the pin to select different rails. For example, moving the pin to the bottom selects all the weight plates. The pin is super strong polypropylene and rated for a 500lbs. max load. Magnets inside the pin hold it securely once inserted completely.
Specifications

Weight Increments: 4 lbs, 8 lbs, 12 lbs, 16 lbs, 20 lbs, 24 lbs, 28lbs, and 32 lbs per hand

Dimensions (LxWxH): 12″ x 5.75″ x 5.5″

* Non-Epandable*
